[\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Australia picked up four gold and two bronze medals on day 12 of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9967512166231871, \"rank\": 0.0032593723713693168, \"text\": \"Team Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 18 gold medals on the board are a record for Australia, surpassing its previous top of 17 set in Athens in 2004 - a result that was repeated in Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9832696267741555, \"rank\": 0.013352638720194637, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8268798324283213e-17, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7812905992299372, \"rank\": 0.279933485676996, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the gold medal winners was pole vaulter Nina Kennedy.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1213, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999997051937023, \"rank\": 2.9480501123675506e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was the only vaulter to clear 4.90m, which saw her claim Australia's 18th gold medal.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9832696267741555, \"rank\": 0.013352638720194637, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's men's team pursuit cycling team beat fierce rivals Great Britain in the final to win the Olympic gold medal for the first time in 20 years.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9832696267741555, \"rank\": 0.013352638720194637, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999846518223, \"rank\": 5.6604736160600585e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skateboarder Keegan Palmer achieved the prodigious feat of spinning and twisting his way to his second Olympic gold medal at the age of 21.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1471, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skateboarding\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3311471104348232e-39, \"text\": \"Skateboarder\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skateboarding\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skateboarding\"}, {\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His win came a day after14-year-old Arisa Trewtook home the gold medal in the women's event.\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Matt Wearn dominated the men's dinghy race in Marseille to collect his second Olympic sailing gold medal.\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"score\": 0.7017643742953025, \"rank\": 0.4249797177349855, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_de_Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won the same event at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sprinter Julien Alfredmade historywhen she won gold in the women's 100m final in Paris.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mercedes-Benz_Sprinter\", \"score\": 0.9999792609841798, \"rank\": 2.0735416659650914e-05, \"text\": \"Sprinter\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mercedes-Benz_Sprinter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mercedes-Benz_Sprinter\"}, {\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251113232221177e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old, from the Caribbean Island nation of St Lucia, not only became the country's first athlete to win an Olympic medal when she won the race, but three days later scored silver for the 200m.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999999919882612, \"rank\": 8.011910013206278e-09, \"text\": \"St Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a population of less than 200,000, Alfred's home country first participated in the 1996 Olympic Games in Atlanta.\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999999992119228, \"rank\": 7.882360258848714e-10, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her time of 10.72 seconds in the 100m also set a national record.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another Caribbean Island nation also celebrated its first Olympic medal - and it was also a gold.\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dominica's Thea LaFond was the only woman in her competition to jump more than 15m in the women's triple jump to claim the medal.\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\", \"score\": 0.9999999971428224, \"rank\": 2.856993181932875e-09, \"text\": \"Dominica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominica\"}, {\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thea LaFond\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thea_LaFond\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would have been a school night forAustralian skateboarder Arisa Trew's friends back home when the 14-year-old competed in the women's park skateboarding final in Paris, on day 11 of the Games.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2640, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6629134109736735e-22, \"text\": \"Arisa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251113232221177e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Cairns-born skater scored 93.18 on her third and final run to beat Japan's Cocona Hiraki who was on 92.63 and Great Britain's Sky Brown on 92.31.\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2847, \"end\": 2852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9342048689147611, \"rank\": 0.07040706652378743, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2890, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://db