\", \"score\": 0.9999999846518223, \"rank\": 5.6604736160600585e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is set to fight for a place in the gold medal match but even if she loses her next bout, Ngamba will have already made history, guaranteed a bronze for her efforts.\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3788, \"end\": 3794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\", \"score\": 0.9698229449136496, \"rank\": 0.03111604567535979, \"text\": \"Ngamba\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ngambaa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before sporting events started, the 2024 Olympic Games had become the first to havean equal number of men and women listed to compete on its schedule.\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony was the first to be staged outside of the main Games stadium, with athletes cruising down the Seine River and the athletic track is purple for the first time at an Olympics.\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is the first Games to have events held so far away from the host city.\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4218, \"end\": 4223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251113232221177e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing events were held 15,716 kilometres away on the French Polynesian Island of Tahiti.\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4379, \"end\": 4385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9986246065260327, \"rank\": 0.00137652